<h3>Sandhi Projects for the Desktop</h3>
The Sandhi Engine and other Sub-projects had initially been developed as a Java Swing application for the Desktop.
<br></br>
Users who intend to Use these programs on their Desktop without the Need of an Internet Connection
can download it now from <a href="http://sarovar.org/projects/sandhiprogram/">http://sarovar.org/projects/sandhiprogram/</a>
<br></br>
Please Note:
<br>
Inorder to use the Desktop Version of these programs(Sandhi, Pratyahara Decoder and Transliterator) 
you have to download the Java Runtime Engine 6.0 or above which is avaiable free at <a href="http://java.sun.com/javase/downloads/index.jsp">http://java.sun.com/javase/downloads/index.jsp</a>.
<br>
<br>
Once you are at this Page scroll to <b>Java Runtime Environment (JRE) 6 Update 5</b> and click on the Download Button Adjacent to it and download-install the Software.
<br>
Once the JRE is installed on your System you can download the Sandhi Program ( inclusive of Pratyahara Decoder ) and the Transliterator as Jar Files.
<br>
The Program will autolaunch by clicking on the Jars.
<br>
Please donot try to unzip the Jar Files.

